**Objective:** [State the primary objective of the review]
**Methods:** [Describe search strategy, inclusion criteria, and analysis approach]
**Results:** [Summarize key findings from reviewed literature]
**Conclusion:** [Present main conclusions and implications]

**Keywords:** [3-5 keywords separated by commas]

## Introduction
- Importance and relevance of the topic
- Historical context and evolution
- Rationale for conducting this review
- Scope and objectives
- Target audience and contribution to the field

## Methods
### Search Strategy
- Databases searched (e.g., PubMed, Scopus, Web of Science)
- Search terms and Boolean operators
- Time period covered
- Language restrictions

### Inclusion and Exclusion Criteria
- Study designs included
- Population characteristics
- Interventions/exposures
- Outcomes considered
- Quality criteria

### Data Extraction and Analysis
- Data extraction process
- Quality assessment tools
- Synthesis methodology (narrative, systematic, meta-analysis)
- Statistical methods (if applicable)

